Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "hitan" in different forms and positions:

1. *Hitan* sam, moram da požurim na sastanak. (I'm in a hurry, I need to rush to a meeting.)
2. Naša kompanija se bavi proizvodnjom *hitnih* medicinskih pomagala. (Our company specializes in producing emergency medical aids.)
3. Hitna pomoć je stigla na mesto nesreće za manje od 10 minuta. (*Emergency* services arrived at the accident site in less than 10 minutes.)
4. Moramo da reagujemo na ovu situaciju *hitno*. (We need to respond to this situation *urgently*.)
5. Vozač je uleteo u krivi smer na *hitan* način, što je dovelo do saobraćajne nesreće. (The driver entered the wrong lane in an *emergency* manner, which led to a traffic accident.)
6. Imamo *hitnu* potrebu za novim članom tima, jer nam nedostaje radne snage. (We have an *urgent* need for a new team member, as we are short-staffed.)
7. *Hitno* je potrebno da promenimo našu strategiju, jer se tržište brzo menja. (It's *urgently* necessary for us to change our strategy, as the market is rapidly changing.)
8. *Hitan* slučaj je prijavljen policiji u vezi sa ovim incidentom. (*An emergency* case has been reported to the police regarding this incident.)

I hope these examples help!